function words_string($str) {
    $words = preg_split('/,| /', $str);
    return $words;
}
```

This function takes a string as input and uses the `preg_split` function to split it into an array of words. The `preg_split` function splits the string based on the regular expression `/,| /`, which means it will split the string by commas or spaces.
